Clark Street Ale House will always be my favorite River North bar. It's probably the only bar in River North with a true neighborhood feel. They have an incredible beer and whiskey selection with their beers always rotating. There is an outdoor patio for seating when it's nice, they have free popcorn and pretzels, the staff is super nice AND they allow dogs in there.  They do not serve food here though, but they do allow you to bring it in from elsewhere. It's a great spot to hangout, watch sports if you want or just catch up with people. It's never too loud and it doesn't get overly crowded.  I wish I could rate them 5/5 over and over again!

Popped in here on the first "winter storm" of the season this year. Flew in from TX (Austin before you judge), had the typical Chicago food fair then wanted to grab a drink at a chill place with good options near the hotel. Thank you yelp for bringing us to Clarke Street.  Walked in around 4 pm. Greeted warm welcome and prompt service. Kasha is fantastic! She was personable, amazing service and gave us great recommendations of places to visit. Ended up hanging out two hours enjoying the vibe and chatting with regulars. Plus free pretzel sticks during the day.  Heck we left after two hours to see the parade and had a terrible experience at a nearby bar / restaurant (sorry, Stout but you're over priced and your food was meh at best). That experience was so crappy (and it was effing cold), we came back to Clark Street...actually hoping to catch Kasha before we left to get better recommendations nearby. She did not disappoint. Even introduced is to the bartenders at Clark St for the next few days since she was off. Talk about making out of towners feel welcome.  They had a great beer selection. The $7 for three beer samplers was great for an out of towner (or someone who doesn't like beer commitment). Overall, good selection of some solid always get and more unique offerings. Other tips, there is a pizza place upstairs that you can order in from.  They also have full hard liquor options. If you want to experience something super local (and probably regret it 15 second later) try melort (spelling?). It's a local moonshine like spirit that tastes great until about 15 seconds after you swallow, in which case you hit bitter town city. But I love a good local experience.  Overall, can't say enough good about our two experiences here. Definitely a must if you're in the area or looking for a place to enjoy a chill beer, come here.
